      "content": "The time gap between when you take the medication and when you consume grapefruit juice isn't guaranteed to prevent the interaction, as the active compounds can be absorbed feed back into your system and still influence the medication's efficacy. While you haven't experienced any problems yet, it's unpredictable, and waiting isn't a foolproof method to avoid potential risks. Regularly consuming grapefruit juice with medication for an extended period could lead to cumulative effects. It's always safest to consult with your healthcare professional even if you've been fine so far to ensure it won't affect you down the line. Your health and safety are the top priorities.",
